node.title: Queensland man vanishes off Sunshine Coast beach, police divers face trecherous conditions
node.alt: An empty wooden table soaked by rain and illuminated next to the darkness of the sea at night
node.description: Two swimmers run into trouble at Shelly Beach at Caloundra, with only one of them rescued.Police divers are hampered in their search by what they describe as "washing machine" conditions.
node.content:
["A 20-year-old Brisbane man has vanished in waters off Queensland's Sunshine Coast, with divers' efforts hampered by what they described as \"washing machine\" conditions.", "Travis Davis and a second person were swimming at Shelley Beach in the late afternoon on Saturday\u00a0when passers-by on the beach saw them begin to struggle.", "Three people entered the water to help the pair, but only one of the swimmers was pulled to safety.", "The second man, also in his 20s, remains in hospital.", "Police diving unit officer in charge Sergeant Andy Bower said the conditions were deceptive.", "\"It looked okay on the surface, but the divers report that underneath it was quite a washing machine, pushing back and forth, which made searching a bit more difficult.\"\u00a0\u00a0", "", "
Sergeant Andy Bower said the\u00a0conditions were \"like a washing machine\"\u00a0beneath the surface.(ABC News: Jacqui Street)
", "The dive team was called into action as it returned from flood-ravaged parts of southern Queensland.", "The search was called off by 9:00pm on Saturday as a severe thunderstorm struck the area.", "Mr Davis's family watched the search unfold from the shoreline.", "Caloundra man Tony Dwyer said he watched the police boats, jet-skis and helicopter search for the man.", "He said the incident happened at what he described as\u00a0a notorious part of the beach.", "\"Most people know not to swim here because it's not patrolled, and there's always rips here,\" he said.", "He said he felt for the young man's family, particularly given how close it was to Christmas.", "", "
Caloundra's Coast Guard assisted with the search in dangerous conditions.\u00a0(ABC News: Jacqui Street)
", "\"It's a terrible thing to happen at any time of the year, but especially now,\" he said.", "\"Everyone has come out of COVID and are trying to get back together as families and something like this happens.\"", "Police\u00a0intend\u00a0to restart the search early on Sunday."]
